(44, 19, 15, 41, 5, 9, 13, 'Jesus I know', 'Recognition of Authority', 'This connection highlights the recognition of Jesus'' authority by evil spirits in both passages. In Acts, the evil spirit acknowledges Jesus and Paul, while in Mark, the unclean spirits identify themselves as Legion, indicating their awareness of Jesus'' power.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 19, 15, 42, 4, 33, 35, 'Jesus I know', 'Recognition of Jesus'' Authority', 'Both passages emphasize the recognition of Jesus'' identity and authority by evil spirits. In Acts, the evil spirit acknowledges Jesus and Paul, while in Luke, the unclean devil recognizes Jesus as ''the Holy One of God.'' This connection highlights the theme of spiritual recognition of divine power.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
